    "description": "Currently, if you use the @derived_field decorator to add a field more than once, yt gives a confusing [error message](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/atmyers/3149d54abe6e6fc9b169). That may look like a weird thing to be doing, but it comes up for me when I define derived fields in a notebook and then try to re-run it using \"Run All Below.\" \r\n\r\nI think that yt should instead warn the user that the field already exists, but not throw an error, like [this](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/atmyers/a4fad490b8e072f1c218). This PR makes that happen, but I'm not sure whether this is the best behavior and/or the best way to implement it, so comments are welcome. ",
